ğŸ”¹ What are Current Events in UPSC?

Current events are recent developments (generally last 12â€“18 months) that affect:

Governance & polity

Economy & social development

Environment & science

Indiaâ€™s relations with the world

ğŸ‘‰ UPSC does NOT ask news directly.
It asks:

Background

Why in news

Constitutional / institutional angle

Impact on India & world

Link with static syllabus

ğŸ”¹ What UPSC actually tests

Policies & schemes (objectives, ministry, beneficiaries)

International organisations & groupings

Reports & indices

Environment conventions

Science & tech applications (not inventions)

ğŸ“Œ Focus = Issue-based understanding, not headlines.

